titleproper.value: Guide to the Martha Wilson Papers, 1950-2016 (bulk 1964-2006) <num>MSS.175</num>

author.value: Collection processed by Lydia Brawner (2011); Finding aid completed by Rachel Greer (2012).

creation.value: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace <date>2019-07-31T19:32:32</date>

abstract.value: The Martha Wilson Papers consist of comprehensive documentation of the life and career of Martha Wilson, artist and Founding Director of Franklin Furnace, Inc. Materials include journals, correspondence, flyers and posters, articles, clippings, juvenilia dating from grade school onward, video recordings, and a computer disc. The collection also contains materials related to Wilson's son Comly Cook-Wilson, and restricted materials dealing with Wilson's finances and medical history.

p.value: The remainder of the collection is open without restrictions.
Identification of item, date; Martha Wilson Papers; MSS 175; box number; folder number; Fales Library and Special Collections, New York University.

Donated by Martha Wilson in 2006. The accession number associated with this gift is 2006.175. Further accretions were donated in 2008-2018. The accession numbers associated with these gifts are 2008.175, 2010.175, 2011.175, 2013.175.001, 2013.175.002, 2015.175,  2017.027, and 2018.093.
---"Conceptual Art and Feminism: Martha Rosler, Adrian Piper, Eleanor Antin, and Martha Wilson": Woman's Art Journal, Vol. 22, No. 1 Spring - Summer, 2001.
Materials date from 1950 to 2017 with the bulk of the materials covering 1964 to 2006.
